Bayern Munich Leads Home Sweep of Victories in Champions League Playoffs

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-08-17T22:49:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/bayern-munich-leads-home-sweep-of-victories-in-champions-league-playoffs.html
Four-time champion  Bayern Munich  led
a sweep of victories for all five home teams in last night’s
 Champions League  soccer playoff openers.  Bayern, whose Allianz Arena will host the May 19, 2012
final, beat FC Zurich 2-0 on goals from Bastian Schweinsteiger
and  Arjen Robben . Dinamo Zagreb, Maccabi Haifa, Odense and Wisla
Krakow also won to take leads into next week’s return games.  The winners of the 10 two-match playoff series will advance
to the 32-team group stage of European soccer’s elite club
competition. Teams received a miniumum of 7.2 million euros
($10.3 million) from tournament organizer  UEFA  for participating
in the the group stage last season.  Arsenal, Lyon and Viktoria Plzen won two days ago, while
BATE Borisov and  FC Twente  rallied for home draws against Sturm
Graz and Benfica, respectively. The return games are scheduled
Aug. 23-24.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  